-- Hitachi Koki Poised to Decline on German Unit's `Improper' Transactions
-- B y   K y u n g   B o k   C h o
-- 2010-10-05T23:39:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-05/hitachi-koki-poised-to-decline-on-german-unit-s-improper-transactions.html
Hitachi Koki Co., a Japanese maker of
electric tools, was poised to decline in Tokyo trading after
saying a German subsidiary had “improper” business
transactions that will affect the parent company’s earnings.  Hitachi Koki shares were bid at 697 yen as of 8:37 a.m. on
the Tokyo Stock Exchange, compared with yesterday’s closing
price of 737 yen.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kyung Bok Cho at 
 kcho7@bloomberg.net  